---
import { shared } from "../data/landing";
---

<section class="bg-page-soft py-20 sm:py-24" aria-labelledby="asset-plan-title">
  <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.72fr_1.28fr] lg:items-end">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm font-extrabold uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-primary">Assets planejados</p>
        <h2 id="asset-plan-title" class="mt-4 text-balance font-display text-3xl font-black tracking-[-0.04em] text-ink sm:text-5xl">
          A landing já reserva espaço para fotos reais quando elas chegarem.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-5 text-lg font-medium leading-8 text-muted">
          Em vez de preencher a página com imagens genéricas, cada bloco abaixo provisiona um tipo específico de prova visual que deve ser produzido para a versão final.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {shared.futureAssets.map((asset) => (
          <article class="rounded-[2rem] border border-border bg-panel p-4 shadow-lift">
            <div class:list={["grid place-items-center rounded-[1.5rem] border border-dashed border-primary/55 bg-primary/8 p-5 text-center", asset.ratio]}>
              <span class="font-display text-5xl font-black text-primary/40">+</span>
            </div>
            <h3 class="mt-5 font-display text-xl font-black tracking-tight text-ink">{asset.title}</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm font-semibold leading-6 text-muted">{asset.description}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
